<!-- AESTHETICS / DESIGN -->

<section id="aesthetics" class="section container">

<h1>Aesthetics & Design</h1>

<div class="row">

<div class="col-md-6">

<img src="images/aesthetic.jpg" class="img-fluid zoom">

</div>

<div class="col-md-6">

<p>
Caribbean aesthetics and design reflect the cultural fusion of African
heritage, indigenous traditions, and contemporary diasporic identity.
Visual culture throughout the Caribbean celebrates vibrant color
palettes, bold patterns, and artistic expression inspired by tropical
landscapes and carnival celebrations.
</p>

<p>
Design appears in architecture, graphic art, fashion, and digital
media. Caribbean creators use rhythm, color, and symbolism to express
cultural pride and community identity.
</p>

<p>
Modern designers continue expanding Caribbean aesthetics through
animation, digital illustration, and creative storytelling that
reaches global audiences.
</p>

</div>

</div>

</section>


<!-- FASHION -->

<section id="fashion" class="section container">

<h1>Fashion</h1>

<div class="row">

<div class="col-md-6">

<img src="images/fashion.jpg" class="img-fluid zoom">

</div>

<div class="col-md-6">

<p>
Caribbean fashion celebrates cultural pride and personal identity.
Designers often combine vibrant fabrics, Afro-Caribbean hairstyles,
and bold color palettes inspired by island environments.
</p>

<p>
Carnival fashion is one of the most recognizable expressions of
Caribbean creativity, featuring elaborate costumes, feathers,
beading, and artistic craftsmanship.
</p>

<p>
Contemporary Caribbean streetwear continues to influence global
fashion trends while celebrating Black heritage and diaspora style.
</p>

</div>

</div>

</section>


<!-- ART -->

<section id="art" class="section container">

<h1>Art</h1>

<div class="row">

<div class="col-md-6">

<img src="images/art.jpg" class="img-fluid zoom">

</div>

<div class="col-md-6">

<p>
Caribbean visual art blends African heritage, indigenous traditions,
and modern perspectives. Artists often explore themes of migration,
memory, and cultural identity.
</p>

<p>
Murals, paintings, sculptures, and digital art capture stories of
community resilience and celebration. Many artists use bold color
contrasts and symbolism to reflect the history and creativity of the
Caribbean diaspora.
</p>

</div>

</div>

</section>


<!-- ANIMATIONS -->

<section id="animations" class="section container">

<h1>Animations</h1>

<div class="row">

<div class="col-md-6">

<img src="images/animation.jpg" class="img-fluid zoom">

</div>

<div class="col-md-6">

<p>
Animation is an emerging creative field for Caribbean artists and
storytellers. Through digital animation, creators can explore folklore,
history, and futuristic visions of Caribbean life.
</p>

<p>
New animation styles often combine 3D modeling with comic or manga
inspired visual techniques to create dynamic storytelling rooted in
Black cultural experiences.
</p>

</div>

</div>

</section>


<!-- MUSIC -->

<section id="music" class="section container">

<h1>Music</h1>

<div class="row">

<div class="col-md-6">

<img src="images/music.jpg" class="img-fluid zoom">

</div>

<div class="col-md-6">

<p>
Music is one of the Caribbean’s most influential cultural exports.
Genres such as reggae, dancehall, soca, and calypso have shaped
global music culture.
</p>

<p>
Caribbean music often carries powerful messages about resistance,
community, celebration, and social awareness.
</p>

<p>
These rhythms and sounds continue to influence artists worldwide.
</p>

</div>

</div>

</section>


<!-- LITERATURE -->

<section id="literature" class="section container">

<h1>Literature</h1>

<div class="row">

<div class="col-md-6">

<img src="images/books.jpg" class="img-fluid zoom">

</div>

<div class="col-md-6">

<p>
Caribbean literature captures the complex history and cultural
identity of the region. Writers explore themes of migration,
colonial history, family, and belonging.
</p>

<p>
Poetry, novels, and storytelling traditions preserve Caribbean
voices and allow global audiences to connect with the experiences
of the Black diaspora.
</p>

</div>

</div>

